i have nothing to write here anymore........

i feel like i have nothing to live for anymore, and that i havent been living.......

the only thing i have been living through is my music.....

its the only way i know how to feel anymore.....



first post in a really long time and it is very emo...
oh well, this is a journal right?

i think i might be through with livejournal for awhile....
so this will probably be my last post for a long time.....

Well happy New Year everyone!!

Last night i went to the Red Wings game with Steph, Renea, David Kullman and a bunch of her friends and family!! it was so much fun and the perfect way to celebrate New Years!! it was the first time i had ever been in a suite and let me say it was.....SWEET! The Wings won 5-2 and i have a new love of hockey! it was a blast and having renea scream "kick em in the face!" always adds to the fun!


<Ok so i stole this from katie!

IN THE YEAR 2005!!!
[P E O P L E]
1. Best friend? Benjamin Christopher Anderson
2. Lost any friends? Not lost, just feel like i am losing touch:-(
3. Gained any friends? Heck Yes!
4. Met a new good friend? Yes, like David Kullman, Blake, Jake, Tasha and Jeremy!
[P L A C E S]
1. Went out of the country? Not this year, but i have!
2. Moved? No.
3. New school? No.
4. How many times on an airplane? None this year!!
5. Road trips? New York and Birmingham(lol)
[Y O U]
1. Have you changed? Yes, a lot!
2. New look? Not really, just new hair now and then!
3. Any new additions? Definately not
4. Biggest conflict this year? Fighting with parents.
5. Most depressed time this year? When my best friend left and when the 05' seniors graduated
[L O V E]
1. Did you fall in love? Yes...
2. Did you get heartbroken? Yes...
3. Who was your summer love? Secret information
4. Favorite date? DSO concerts
5. Did you turn someone down? Kind of.
[S E A S O N S]
1. Favorite Season? Spring
2. Good birthday? Heck yea! i had the best birthday ever! Decorated locker, balloons, David Kullman playing me happy birthday on his trumpet, the football game, laura's party and its just where my year started for me! how could it get any better than that.
3. Any snow this year? Duh, this is michigan
4. Highest temperature? I dont know...think back to how miserable we are at band camp, that always works!
[F I N A L Q U E S T I O N S]
1.Met a person who will change your life? Yea...
2.Kept your resolution? I dont even know if i had a resolution
3.Had a first something? ummmm..yea
4.Smoked weed/drugs? Absolutley not!!
5.Did anything illegal? ummmmm...dont know
6.Liked someone who didn't like you? Yes.
7.Changed your view on things? ALOT!!
8.One thing that you regret? Never have regrets...never hold back!
9.One thing you will never forget? Yea...like these last 4 months
10.Who will you thank in 2005 for making a difference in your life? I would like to thank all of my friends!! i love you all to death!!

2005 was and ahhhmazing year, and if i wanted anything for 2006, i would say keep all of the above!!
and i guess that will be my resolution too! But of course i have little resolutions that only i know!hehe.

The Lord answered my prayer yesterday....

the greatest thing just made my day!

Thats it...

Au Bientot!

Michelle

wow so i am really bored....

i had to wake up at 5:30 this morning so that my mom could clean my teeth, and give me my check up...sometimes i hate having parents in the medical field, but at other times, i cheerish it!

i have been updating my ipod with all of the new CD's i just got! it takes forever though.

-----------------
i miss his family
i miss church
i miss everything
...i miss Benny


everything really does feel different.......nothing can ever replace it

Well Merry Christmas Everyone!! i hope santa got you all what you wished for....

Santa brought me a digital camera this year!! i was so happy..its a canon and super small...way cute!! i also got some clothes, money, CD's and all that good stuff too!!
(steph, must go shopping!..how about someday after weds..when i have gotten my paycheck!)

I got a call from my Uncle in England today..it is so much fun to talk to him on the phone, eventhough he is extremely hard to understand, its always a good chat!

Today my aunt and uncle from delaware came over, its always good to see them.

Yesterday was Christmas Eve Dinner at my Aunts house...We had a very festive polish meal, it was pretty cool....all homemade stuff too, so thats always good. Then it was off to church, and wow what a good service this year, they have really updated everything (music wise)...and the rev. always tells the story better and better every year.

Well thats about it...i have to work tomorrow..ahh can you believe it, at 8 in the A.M...oh well, its money...

HAVE A GREAT REST OF YOUR BREAK EVERYONE!!!

<3michelle

there will always be that one thing i wish i could have done today....
i miss it all...

HORRAY FOR BAND CONCERTS.....!!!!!


SO EXCITED FOR TONIGHT!!


AND GREAT JOB TO BECCAH RATHAUS FOR WINNING US THE DOOR DECORATING CONTEST...YAY!!

SEE MOST OF YOU TONIGHT!!


MICHELLE

Wow i really want a snow day tomorrow!  There is so much snow on the ground!

Oh and i am so sad that the concert got canceled for tonight:-( i was really looking forward to it.....but on the plus side, it has been rescheduled for next tues, so everyone come, it is sure to be a fun time!

well so since i have like no HW, i think i am going to go get some christmas shopping done!....ttyl.

michelle

i miss everything....its going to be hard.......

well today was the day....my last day to see Benny(Elder Anderson)before he leaves on his wonderful journey. I went to church with him one last time this morning and his whole family was there. it was so nice, i love every single member of his family. it was a great way to say goodbye. i have to say though i will miss the long 1 am phone calls, DSO concerts, random things that we do with eachother, spending time with his family and him in general. I do agree though that 2 years will go by faster than you know it especially since it is my senior year that is coming up soon. 

i just know that he is doing what he believes in, and will succeed in anything that he does. every ounce of luck to you Benny, and i will see you in 2 years. dont forget about me.

michelle

so as i already said, yesterday was a snowday!! YEAH for snowdays!!!

i woke up at 11:30 and did some X-mas shopping..then i went to benny's open house, which was really fun! i had a great time!

then this morning, i couldnt sleep and i woke up at 8:00, and then i went to borders a little bit later and bought some classical.  good stuff! then i practiced for a long time only forgetting that i left half of my music at school, i wonder if it is open today? and now i am just extremely bored.........but i am having a great 3 DAY weekend so far, so its all good! well i guess i will go find something to do.........

ttyl
<3michelle

Yea for snow days!!!!!!!!!!

so i did a little bit more christmas shopping today, i am almost done, i just got to get my paycheck so that i have a little more money!!

now i shall be off....hope everyone has a great weekend...ttyl!!

<3michelle

well i must go now.......rehearsal from 6-7 tonight for antiphonal (sp?) brass, fun fun!....hope everyone has a wonderful day!!

today was such a good day...

i actually got some sleep and i watched a movie and then i went to borders and just sat there and read random books...its just so relaxing for me...especially if you find one of those like secret spots where no one is...like in the art section...i know, i know, im a loser...but you know what, i dont care what people think about me.

and now i am just really bored...so i guess i will talk to everyone later.

<3 michelle

so today i got up a 6:30 to drive up to Lawrence Tech University for their campus visit day.  Lets just say i didnt want to be there, but it really wasnt as bad as i thought it was going to be...yea i would have much rather been doing other things...but it was pretty eye opening.  Realizing now that it really is time to start looking at colleges and figuring out my life...its kind of scary.  It did though, cement into my mind, that i want to go into some kind of design.  They had a great program, but i think it is just lacking the college life that i want, like living on my own and kind of away from home so i can get a taste of real life.  They also dont have a music program or any kind of music for that fact and that is just a neccessity in my life.  For one i want to minor in music performance and without music, life would just not be worth living for me.  It is like my mind, body and soul.  But yea so that was pretty much the highlight of my day, and wow it really got me thinking about life and just everything that is going to happen in my future.

then i came home, and just practiced my clarinet forever...i was having to much fun with Molly on the Shore.

then it was parade time, and eh it was same old, same old.

well thats about it...have a good relaxing sunday everyone.

<3 michelle
10 more days...

wow so today had to be one of the best school days ever.....

i mean yea i had a really bad headache all day, and a crazy geometry test...but then i got to band and it was all worth it!!

So first thing, i walk in the band room and there is a new piece on my stand....didnt think much of it at first, but then i saw it, and thought "ARE YOU KIDDING ME...ITS CARMINA BURANA!!!!!!!"...only one of my favorite pieces of music!!! its one thing to be able to listen to it, but play it, its a whole different ball game...i never thought i was going to be able to play that song in HS, but wow i am!!........and let me just tell ya, its ahhhhmazing to play!

then came the big one of the day.....Mr. Steele pulls me into his office, and says "congratulations, you made the All-State Honors Band!"...ahhhhhhhhhh...i was so happy i couldnt believe it...out of 180 clarinets who auditioned, i got picked! after all the stress i put myself through to audition, it is one of the biggest accomplishments i have had in music, and i am just so happy!! Best part is, i get to go to grand rapids, stay in a hotel for three days and see 2 amazing symphonies when i am there!! this is just going to be such an eye opening experience, and i am so excited!

well thats about it for now, i hope everyone stays safe on those slippery roads.
have a fun weekend!

<3 michelle

right....im in a very randomish mood today!! and i dont really know why, but i like it!!

my car is so dirty...my stupid self decided to go down scripps this morning with it have been raining the night before...so basically my car looks like it went through a giant pool of mud and then it got all dried and caked on....whoa ok so enough about my car!

i am so glad that my hard work in school is paying off too!! i have had the best two progress reports i have ever had...A,A,A-,A-!! im so happy those are my grades right now...im actually doing good in math...me? good in math? no..i never thought it was possible!

i wore a really random shirt today too...i got it at the salvation army and it says turnstyle on it...i heard it was some kind of band but if anyone has any suggestions to what it means, then i will gladly take them...cuz i know what a turnstyle is, but just not why it would be on a shirt. i guess it is one of those mysterious questions of the world.

i love what we are playing in band...the songs are so good and full of emotion! im so happy...i think i have worked everything out!!

now this is a serious fact...i really need more classical music, but ahhhhh i am so broke...i dont know where it all went...really i dont!!

and i have lessons tomorrow...hopefully i can work out scaramouche a little bit better for shelly!!

well wow..today the lord was definately on my side and blessed me with a happy day..hopefully it will be just as wonderful tomorrow!
have a great day!

<3 michelle

~"Ask and it will be given to you; seek and you will find; knock and the door will be opened to you. For everyone who asks receives, he who seeks finds; and to him who knocks, the door will be opened."
      
~"So long as we are loved by others I should say that we are almost indispensable; and no man is useless while he has a friend."

~"People are unreasonable, illogical and self-centered. 
Love them anyway.
If you do good, people will accuse you of selfish, ulterior motives. 
Do good anyway. 
If you are successful, you will win false friends and true enemies. 
Succeed anyway.
The good you do today will be forgotten tomorrow. 
Do good anyway. 
Honesty and frankness make you vulnerable. 
Be honest and frank anyway.
The biggest person with the biggest ideas can be 
shot down by the smallest person with the smallest mind. 
Think big anyway. 
What you spend years building may 
be destroyed overnight. 
Build anyway. 
People really need help but may attack if you help them. 
Help people anyway. 
Give the world the best you have 
and you might get kicked in the teeth. 
Give the world the best you've got anyway."

~"The meeting of two personalities is like the contact of two chemical substances: if there is any reaction, both are transformed."

~"Too often we underestimate the power of a touch, a smile, a kind word, a listening ear, an honest compliment, or the smallest act of caring, all of which have the potential to turn a life around." 

~"Friendship is a single soul dwelling in two bodies."

~"Good listeners, like precious gems, are to be treasured."

~"take the happy with the sad, the good with the bad, laugh like you mean it and live life to the fullest."


michelle

this morning i woke up and went to work for 3 hrs from 8-11...it was really wierd feeling! lol dont even know why.

but anyway...last night i went to the DSO with Benny! honestly it had to be one of the best DSO concerts i have ever seen...yea call me a band geek, i dont care, but that music was so beautiful and moving and so full of emotion that it actually moved me to tears...i mean adagio for strings(do i even have to say anything) and then lincoln portrait was amazing with the actual words of abe lincoln being spoken while you listen to the music....ahhh it was just sooo good...........oh and we also got all snazzied up and went to macaroni grill...it was sweet, i got to draw on the table...pretty tight eh?

so in a way..my tears were happy tears of just hearing beautiful music, but it also made me think...which with me can sometimes not be a good thing...but at least someone was able to turn my tears into laughter.

i think thats about it for now....i am very bored....blah.

michelle

...i can now turn my weaknesses into strengths, i am stronger now....

"friends are like quiet angels who lift you up when you have forgotten how to fly"

hey happy thanksgiving everyone!!

i know i am definately thankful for a lot of things on this day and know that i am truely blessed with everything that i have and have achieved.

have a wonderful rest of your break everyone!

wow what to say.....

so this was pretty much one of the best weekends ever!

friday i went to the away game, got lost and really frustrated on the way home, but thankfully found my way and besides the game was to much fun and even though we lost, our boys are amazing!

then sat i had to work, from 8 in the am till 4 in the pm, which really wasnt that bad.  it was a pretty easy day...i was like the cook all morning at breakfast, and then i was in back booth in DT and then front DT which is my fave place to be. then i asked heather if i could get off work a half hour early and she let me go, so that was a half hour earlier that i got to see benny and give him his birthday present and just hang out with him for 2 hours.

then sunday was just the greatest! everything was just so nice and so much fun...going to church with benny in the morning and listening to him speak was so great and then going to his dads house for the rest of the night and just spending a night with him and his family was so nice. i was just so happy that i got to spend such a wonderful day with my best(to infinity!)friend on his birthday. and we def cannot forget the crazy being blown off the road car ride and amazing russian music on the way home.

so all in all it was a fun, exciting, special, rejuvinating and relaxing weekend that i never wanted to end.

i hope everyone else had just as much fun on their three day weekend!

later!

<3 michelle

michelle

so i actually decided to keep updating....

well im so happy that i am back to my normal self....i love band...it feels so good to be back in syphonic band..."MARCHE SLAVE" is my hero...it rocks my sox.

i really need to go out and buy some more classical music...there is so much that i love, i just never have the chance to go out and get it...i will have to go with you (Benny) since you know all of the good stuff!

......"music washes away from the soul, the dust of everyday life"......

...sometimes, just writing down all of your feelings and talking it out with someone you care about can be the best medicine for an aching heart and a stirred up mind...

me

so friday was defintately the only good thing about my weekend...from sat on...it was just well....crap:-(

But on the bright side, on fri, Benny and I had an amaaaaazing time at the DSO...taking a tour of all of these gorgeous houses that he cuts the grass for was amazing..they were sooo big, thanks Benny!  Then stopping at a Ghetto Wendys in Detroit before hte concert...lets just say that was well..interesting...then the concert...what can i say...it was just glorious...I have a new love for all Russian composers...yea i went to see Rachmaninov, but the Hindemith was absolutely wonderful...and the seats...i have to say i did good...front row!!! lol

then sat...competition...ehhhh

well i dont really want to talk about the rest of my weekend unless it is to yours truly and you know who you are ;-)

well off to MB practice...talk to you all later.

michelle

P.S. if i dont talk to you later, it was a lot better! ;-)
ahhhhhhhhhh...what is wrong with me.........i wish i could just go back.....

so i havent updated in awhile, and i dont really need to talk about last weekend, since everybody already has, but i am still going to do it anyway...

last weekend was definately one of the best weekends that i have ever had!  The friday night football game was amazing.  It was so cool being down on the field while the team beat clarkston!! our show went pretty well too!  Then after the game, i went over to Benny's house for a little while, and he showed me all of his "pimptastic" suits! then we hit the band party together and listened to some sweet music on the way.  The best part there, was when we took a picture, and there was a third head...dum dum dum! haha..after the pary, i went back to his house and we sat in his car for a little while and listened to some more amazing music.........i wish i could have more days like that...........i wish life could always be that simple and that happy........

Saturday we went to the great lakes invitational...nothing much to say there, except that we kicked some major boootay! 3rd place, great job guys...i got home at around 12:30, and had another great 1 am conversation. 

Now..back to the present..last night i went to benny's to hang out and we just sat in his room and talked and listened to music...so much fun..brought back alot of great memories...ahhh i love music....Mahler 2!!! most amazingly beautiful piece of music i have ever heard.

FRIDAY.......DSO........Symphonic Dances...cant wait!!

Well this is really long and i am in school, but i just needed to right down my thoughts.

take care everyone...
michelle

i got this from jackie.....

A guy and a girl both best friend chatting online

girl- hey
guy- hey
girl-whats up
guy-nothing, i have some really bad news
girl- what is it?
guy- im moving
girl-you cant move
guy- i am my parents are making me. were moving out of state
girl-you cant go. i'll miss you to much
guy- i know i'll miss you too
girl-i love you
guy-i know, i love you to
guy-i g2g now
guy-later

the girl was sad. not only because he was moving but because he didnt love her the way that she loved him. she had been in love with him since the day they met.

they meet for pizza the day before he leaves. they talk and the girl is worried that she wont ever see him again or that he wont remember her. but the guy promised that he would never forget her and that he would come and visit. they were about to leave when the girl said i love you again. the guy said i know i love you too. we'll be friends forever. although the girl was glad they were friends she was torn up inside that he didnt love her the way she loved him.

he moved the next day. when he got to his new place he got online

girl-hey
girl- i want to tell you something
guy-can it wait i dont feel like talking now

it went on like that for a few weeks. then he stoped talking to her completely. she never got to tell him what she wanted.

the guy came back to visit a year later. the girl ran up and gave him a hug

girl- i missed you so much
guy-do i know you
girl- funny, im your best friend
guy- i dont think i know you. please get away from me now

this destroyed her. she decided to leave. just then a car came around the corner. it was about to hit the guy. the girl ran and jumped in front of the car pushing the guy out of the way. the girl was dead. the guy was invited to her funeral not knowing why he was there since he thought he didnt know her. just then her dad read the last entry out of her diary.

it read: my best friend has moved away. he has stopped talking to me online. i am very sad. i fell in love with him the day we met. but he did not love me the way that i did. i tryed to tell him how i really felt but he didnt want to talk to me. he finally quit talking to me all together. i havent heard from him in months. i miss him dearly. i never got to tell him that i really do love him and that i would do anything for him. even die for him.

just then the guy remembered who she was. he felt horrible. he had forgoten her. he broke his promise
